# ==============================================================================

# .dvcignore — SpectraMind V50 (NeurIPS 2025 Ariel Data Challenge)

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Purpose:

# • Prevent DVC from scanning ephemeral / reproducible files, caches, CI outputs

# • Speed up `dvc status` / `dvc repro` by scoping to true data/model artifacts

# • Keep Git, Docker, Kaggle, Hydra, and ML ecosystem ignores aligned

# • Ensure secrets and transient outputs are never versioned

#

# Notes:

# • .dvcignore affects what DVC scans; it does NOT affect Git. Track true

# datasets/models via `dvc add` and keep ephemeral/generated bits ignored here.

# • Keep this file logically in sync with: .gitignore, .dockerignore

# ==============================================================================

